qas.question: The Skylab 1 was launched on which date?
How much did the Skylab 1 weigh?
When did the Skylab 1 finally come back to Earth?

context: The United States launched the orbital workstation Skylab 1 on <a0_0>May 14, 1973<a0_0/>. It weighed <a1_0>169,950 pounds<a1_0/> (77,090 kg), was 58 feet (18 m) long by 21.7 feet (6.6 m) in diameter, with a habitable volume of 10,000 cubic feet (280 m3). Skylab was damaged during the ascent to orbit, losing one of its solar panels and a meteoroid thermal shield. Subsequent manned missions repaired the station, and the final mission's crew, Skylab 4, set the Space Race endurance record with 84 days in orbit when the mission ended on February 8, 1974. Skylab stayed in orbit another five years before reentering the Earth's atmosphere over the Indian Ocean and Western Australia on <a2_0>July 11, 1979<a2_0/>.
